Demo template for custom subobject display (Level 4 in
docs/user-guide/customizing-display.md).

Book's Chapter subobject field sets
`has_subobject_display_template = ChapterTable`, so the Book dispatcher
routes the whole Chapter section here instead of invoking the default
per-instance Chapter/subobject-row pipeline. Result: all chapters
appear as rows of one shared wikitable, not as a stack of separate
mini-tables.

Parameters:
* category - The subobject category name (passed by the dispatcher).
             Defaults to "Chapter" for direct invocation.
* page     - The parent page whose subobjects to render; defaults to
             {{FULLPAGENAME}}.
